4. COMPETITIVE LANDSCAPE & EXISTING GAPS
---------------------------------------------------------
- Govt of India Solutions:
  * National Cyber Crime Reporting Portal (cybercrime.gov.in) -> Reporting only, reactive.
  * ISEA Stay Safe Online (staysafeonline.in) -> Campaigns, quizzes, awareness packs.
  * e-SafeHER (Reliance/C-DAC) -> Multilingual awareness training for SHGs.
  * PMGDISHA (pmgdisha.in) -> General digital literacy training.
- Civil Society Solutions:
  * Digital Shakti 5.0 (digitalshakti.org) -> Interactive workshops, training programs.
  * TechSakhi Helpline (techsakhi.in) -> Multilingual support helpline for abuse.
- The Gap: All existing systems are either educational campaigns, general courses, training workshops, or post-incident reporting systems. None act as a real-time, proactive, on-device companion guiding users dynamically when permissions are requested.

---------------------------------------------------------
5. PROPER TECH STACK (SECURE MOBILE APP FOCUS)
---------------------------------------------------------
- Core Development Language: Kotlin (safety-first native code) and Java (compatibility layer).
- UI Framework: Jetpack Compose (highly responsive declarative UI, smooth gradient transitions, and direct haptic integration).
- Interception Engine: Android Accessibility Service API (AccessibilityService) to intercept and parse permission overlay layouts.
- Database & Encryption: Room Persistence Library built on top of SQLCipher (AES-256 hardware-accelerated encryption at rest).
- Key Management: Android Keystore System + StrongBox Keymaster (isolates cryptographic keys from application space).
- Authenticity & Verification: Google Play Integrity API (real-time package/device signature attestation to prevent sideloaded fake APK runs).
- Translation & Local Verification: Signature verification (Ed25519 / ECDSA) to authenticate offline translation packs and SQLite rule databases at startup.
- Offline Audio & Haptics: Android Text-to-Speech (TTS) API restricted to offline engines via XML network security config; Android Haptic Feedback API.
- Anomaly & Behavioral Engine: TensorFlow Lite (TFLite) for lightweight, on-device anomaly detection and behavioral modeling, backed by a local Kotlin Finite State Machine (FSM) for velocity/escalation limits.

